description.narrative:
•	Eight out of 10 children in Malawi do not eat adequate, diverse and nutritious diets (Millennium Development Goals Report 2014). In Malawi, such shocks disproportionately affect women and children -these conditions can lead to deterioration of the already precarious nutrition related risks as follows
•	Reduced immunity that leads to an increased risk of morbidity and susceptibility to infection for the general population especially children under-five, pregnant and lactating women, people living with HIV and  AIDs and the elderly;
•	Rapid onset and progression of disease; 
•	Adverse birth outcomes, such a low birth weight and poor growth achievement for the under-five children;
•	Low work capacity for livelihood and resilience activities for the general population due to a combination of anemia and limited energy from having infrequent meals;
•	Reduced learning attention for the school going children;
•	Reduced lactating capacity for breastfeeding women;
•	Absconding from services in search of food.
